 models (2004) Mon. Wea. Rev., 132, pp. 2293-2307; Lin, S.-J., Rood, R.B., Multidimensional flux-form semi-Lagrangian transport schemes (1996) Mon. Wea. Rev., 124, pp. 2046-2070; Meehl, G., Covey, C., Delworth, T., Latif, M., McAvaney, B., Mitchell, J., Stouffer, R., Taylor, K., The WCRP CMIP3 multimodel dataset: A new era in climate change research (2007) Bull. Amer. Meteor. Soc., 88, pp. 1383-1394; Oouchi, K., Yoshimura, J., Yoshimura, H., Mizuta, R., Kusunoki, S., Noda, A., Tropical cyclone climatology in a globalwarming climate as simulated in a 20 km mesh global atmosphericmodel: Frequency and wind intensity analysis (2006) J. Meteor. Soc. Japan, 84, pp. 259-276; Park, S., Bretherton, C.S., The University of Washington shallow convection and moist turbulence schemes and their impact on climate simulations with the Community Atmosphere Model (2009) J. Climate, 22, pp. 3449-3469; Putman, W.M., Lin, S.-J., Finite-volume transport on various cubed-sphere grids (2007) J. Comput. Phys., 227, pp. 55-78; Rayner, R., Parker, D., Horton, E., Folland, C., Alexander, L., Rowel, D., Global analyses of sea surface temperature, sea ice, and night marine air temperature since the late nineteenth century (2003) J. Geophys. Res., 108, p. 4407. , doi:10.1029/2002JD002670; Reynolds, R., Rayner, N., Smith, T., Stokes, D., Wang, W., An improved in situ and satellite SST analysis for climate (2002) J. Climate, 15, pp. 1609-1625; Santer, B.D., Consistency of modelled and observed temperature trends in the tropical troposphere (2008) Int. J. Climatol., 28, pp. 1703-1722. , doi:10.1002/joc.1756; Saunders, M., Lea, A., Large contribution of sea surface warming to recent increase in Altantic hurricane activity (2008) Nature, 451, pp. 557-561. , doi:10.1038/nature06423; Schade, L., Emanuel, K., The ocean's effect on the intensity of tropical cyclones: Results from a simple coupled atmosphere-ocean model (1999) J. Atmos. Sci., 56, pp. 642-651; Sobel, A., Held, I., Bretherton, C., The ENSO s